The paper proposes a new method for recommendation with graphs among users/items, which involves matrix completion and graph convolutional networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers topics related to matrix completion and deep learning. The paper also involves recommendation systems, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses graph convolutional networks, which could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on real datasets, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
